description.text: this message file contains message for s5nmap package

msg.text: PLLREFCS component '$$s' is used with EHXPLLM component '$$s'. The PLLREFCS component PLLCSOUT output signal '$$s' can only drive the CLKI pin of a single EHXPLLM instance.
$$s The device has only $$d EHXPLLM / PLLREFCS resources. The design requirement exceeds available resources.
$$s '$$s' has mismatching FREQUENCY preference value of $$1.1f MHz and its HFCLKOUT output value of $$1.1f MHz based on HFCLKDIV setting of $$d.
$$s '$$s' has mismatching FREQUENCY preference value of $$1.3f MHz and its LFCLKOUT output value of $$5.3f MHz.
Property 'HFCLKDIV' is missing in $$s component '$$s'.Using default value of $$d.
Invalid IO_TYPE assignment of '$$s' for MIPI buffer '$$s' (for $$s port). Cannot change IO_TYPE on MIPI buffer.
The PMUWKUP pin of $$s component '$$s' has invalid connection via signal '$$s'. The PMUWKUP pin should be left unconnected when I2C_ID is set to I2C1.
Invalid load '$$s' connected to MIPI high speed signal '$$s'. MIPI high speed signal can drive IDDR or ECLKSYNC components.\n
PMU '$$s' I2CEN should be DISABLED when PMUWKUP port is tied to GND.\n
PMU '$$s' I2CEN is ENABLED but PMUWKUP port is not connected to I2C.\n
PMU '$$s' EXTEN should be DISABLED when PMUWKUPN port is tied to VCC.\n
PMU '$$s' EXTEN is ENABLED but PMUWKUPN port is not connected to external port.\n
I2C component '$$s' has invalid I2C_CLK_DIVIDER setting of $$d. The valid setting can be from $$d to $$d.\n
Delay component '$$s' has mismatching DEL_MODE '$$s' when its connected IO buffer has IO_TYPE=$$s and its input DDRX2, DDRX4 or DDRX8 usage. DEL_MODE is adjusted to '$$s'.\n
Delay component '$$s' has mismatching DEL_MODE '$$s' when its connected IO buffer has IO_TYPE=$$s $$s without any input DDRX2, DDRX4, or DDRX8 usage. DEL_MODE is adjusted to '$$s'.\n
Delay component '$$s' has mismatching DEL_MODE '$$s' when its connected IO buffer doesn't have IO_TYPE=$$s. DEL_MODE is adjusted to '$$s'.\n
